unread algorithm:
- available information per newsgroup:
	- all message numbers
	- newest message number
	- numbers of all topics
- on page view:
	- common message infos: newest message id, topic tree
	- user infos: newest message id on last visit, pair of (topic-nr : message-nr)
	  meaning: in topic [topic-nr] all messages since [message-nr] are new/unread.
	
	- look at the last known message number:
		- if it's older than the newest message number
			- load all topic pairs
			- iterate over all topics in the message tree
				- if there is a pair for this topic use that pair (the user has unread
				  message in there anyway so the newer ones are marked unread, too).
				- if theres no pair for the topic look if the topic contains a message
				  newer than the last known message number. if so store a pair for
				  it (tnr:mnr).
				- stop after [max-pairs] pairs have been stored and replace the old
				  tracking information with the new pairs
		- else do nothing

- on messages view
	- regenertate tracking pairs
	- remove pair of current topic

- on newsgroups view
	- required info: tracking data, newsgroup high watermark
	
	- read tracking info for all newsgroups
	- if newest message number newer than the tracked one
		- highlight for new messages
	- else
		- if there are tracking pairs for the newsgroups: highlight
		- else nothing new